JOHANNESBURG - Sentiment in the manufacturing sector has taken a beating.Absa s Purchasing Managers Index has dropped by 4.8 points to 46.7 points. Anything below 50 points indicates a contraction of the sector.READ: Manufacturing sector could boost job creation, mean expertsThe bank says it s probably due to continuing uncertainty about the future of the local economy.It says businesses are pessimistic following the technical recession, declining business confidence and political uncertaintyAbsa s also warning about the possibility of strike action in the steel and engineering sectors.eNCA